devdoc.details: This quoter is gas-optimized for on-chain usage and provides mathematically identical results to the official Algebra QuoterV2 by using the same PriceMovementMath library

params._factory: The address of the Algebra factory
params._tickSpacingDeployers: The addresses of tick spacing deployers

params.tokenA: The first token of the pair
params.tokenB: The second token of the pair

returns._0: The address of the most liquid pool, or address(0) if none found

params.amountSpecified: The amount of the swap, which implicitly configures the swap as exact input or exact output
params.poolAddress: The address of the pool to quote against
params.sqrtPriceLimitX96: The Q64.96 sqrt price limit. If zero for one, the price cannot be less than this value after the swap. If one for zero, the price cannot be greater than this value after the swap
params.zeroForOne: Whether the amount in is token0 or token1

returns.amount0: The amount0 delta of the swap
returns.amount1: The amount1 delta of the swap

params.amountIn: The amount of the first token to swap
params.path: The path of the swap, i.e. each token pair encoded as (token0, token1)

returns.amountOut: The amount of the last token that would be received

params.params: The parameters necessary for the swap, encoded as QuoteExactInputSingleParams

returns.amountOut: The amount of the output token that would be received

tickSpacingDeployers.details: Array of tick spacing deployers for finding the most liquid pool

devdoc.title: Algebra Integral Static Quoter

getPool(address,address).notice: Finds the most liquid pool for a token pair across all deployers

quote(address,bool,int256,uint160).notice: Returns the amount0 delta and amount1 delta for a given swap

quoteExactInput(bytes,uint256).notice: Returns the amount out received for a given exact input multi-hop swap without executing the swap

quoteExactInputSingle((address,address,u.notice: Returns the amount out received for a given exact input swap without executing the swap

userdoc.notice: Provides quotes for swaps against Algebra Integral pools using native Algebra math
